.** === Extended help =================================================
.*
:HELP NAME='DSPINFSCR'.
.*
Display Midas Information screen  - Help
:P.
Note that this help text applies to both the DSPINFSCR and SHWINFSCR
commands.  The former is intended for calling from a command line for
testing purposes.  The latter is for coding into CL programs.
:p.
Both commands call the program UTC1000, which puts a list of message IDs
into a form in which they can be displayed on a Midas Information
screen.  The user passes the message IDs, and also the name of the Midas
Information screen handling program, to the command.
:p.
See the Support and Development Guide (BBN16002), Midas Information
Screens section, for more information.
:EHELP.
.*
.** === End of extended help ==========================================
.*
.** === Help for return code ==========================================
.*
:HELP NAME='DSPINFSCR/RETURNCODE'.
Return code (RETURNCODE) - Help
:XH3.
Return code (RETURNCODE)
:P.
This parameter is not visible in DSPINFSCR.  In SHWINFSCR it must contain
the name of a CL variable which will receive the return code from the
program.  The variable must be defined as 10 alpha.  It will be blank if
processing was successful.  It will contain the string 'ERROR' if there
was any problem.
:EHELP.
.*
.** === End of help for Return code ===================================
.*
.** === Help for caller ===============================================
.*
:HELP NAME='DSPINFSCR/CALLER'.
Calling program (CALLER) - Help
:XH3.
Calling program (CALLER)
:P.
Enter the name of the program that is executing this command.  This is
the name which will appear on the Midas Information screen in the From:
field.
:ehelp.
.** === End of help for caller ========================================
.*
.** === Help for messages =============================================
.*
:HELP NAME='DSPINFSCR/MESSAGE1'.
.*
Messages (MESSAGE1 - 10) - Help
.*
:XH3.
.*
Messages (MESSAGE1 - 10)
:P.
Enter up to 10 valid message IDs which exist in the file GBMIDASMSG.
These messages should contain the lines of text that you want to appear
on the screen.  Each should contain no more than 50 characters of text.
Any characters after the 50th will not be displayed.
:p.
Leave message ID fields blank to cause blank lines to appear on the
screen.
:EHELP.
