.** === Help for help indicator =======================================
.*
:help name='DSPINFSCR/HELPIND'.
.*
Help indicator (HELPIND) - Help
.*
:XH3.
.*
Help indicator (HELPIND)
:P.
This field requires a two-digit numeric value which defines which of the
99 possible help tags will be enabled for the Midas Information screen
you specify.
:p.
See the Support and Development Guide (BBN16002), Midas Information
Screens section, for more information on use of the help indicator.
:p.
Note that not all Midas Information screens will have all 99 values
defined.  If you leave this parameter blank, or enter a value which does
not relate to a defined help tag, the user will see the default Midas
Information screen help if they press the help key.
:ehelp.
.** === End of help for help indicator ================================
.*
.** === Help for program to call ======================================
.*
:help name='DSPINFSCR/CALLED'.
.*
Progam to call (CALLED) - Help
.*
:XH3.
.*
Program to call (CALLED)
:P.
Enter the name of the Midas Information program which is to display your
messages on the screen.  You should use the one specific to the module
you are working on.
:ehelp.
.** === End of help for program to call ===============================
.*
.** === Help for option ==============================================
.*
:help name='DSPINFSCR/OPTION'.
.*
Screen format to use (OPTION) - Help
.*
:XH3.
.*
Screen format to use (OPTION)
:P.
Enter the name of the Midas Information screen format that should be
displayed.  The allowed values are:
:PARML.
.** Make 'ENTER' appear as a programming keyword
:PT.:PK DEF.ENTER:EPK.
:PD.
The format requesting the user to press enter to continue will be
displayed.
.*
.** Make the other parameters appear as parameter variables
.*
:PT.:PV.BLANK:EPV.
.*
:PD.
The format which returns control to the calling program without waiting
for a key to be pressed is displayed.
.*
:PT.:PV.JOBLOG:EPV.
:PD.
.*
The format giving the user the option of displaying the job log is
displayed.
.*
:PT.:PV.OPTION:EPV.
:PD.
.*
The format giving the user a Y/N reply option is displayed.
.*
:PT.:PV.OPTION2:EPV.
:PD.
.*
The format giving the user a one character reply option is displayed.
.*
:PT.:PV.RETRY:EPV.
:PD.
.*
The format giving the user a 'Do you wish to retry? (Y/N)' message and
option is displayed.
.*
:EPARML.
:ehelp.
.** === End of help for option ========================================
.*
.** === Help for reply value ==========================================
.*
:help name='DSPINFSCR/REPLY'.
.*
CL var for reply value (REPLY) - Help
.*
:XH3.
.*
CL var for reply value (REPLY)
:P.
This parameter is not visible in DSPINFSCR.  In SHWINFSCR it must contain
the name of a 1-alpha CL variable.  The value it contains when passed to
the command will become the default reply value if one of the
reply-capable formats is displayed.  On return it will contain the reply
that the user entered.
:ehelp.
